CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 27, 1957, pg. A12, reads: "NAACP Awards - Louis Mason Jr., chairman of the NAACP's 1957 membership campaign, presents trophies to (left to right) Irving Beaufford, Matthew Moore and Theodore Jones, for securing 100 members or more. Mr. Moore was tops with 180 members and $543.50; James K. Anderson was second highest with 183 members and $460; Mr. Jones reported 182 members and $420.93 and Mrs. Beaufford reported 150 members and $304.36. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Louis Mason Jr. presenting trophies to Irving Beaufford, Matthew Moore and Theodore Jones for securing memberships in NAACP campaign
